{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"PASS-1 review (A1 anti-slop / over-engineering / NIH): CLEAN — no findings.\n\nAffirmations:\n- NIH avoided: the plan reconstructs coverage['metrics'] from existing recorder step timings (interpreter.py `duration_ms` on leaf/batch steps, persisted via executor.py `_step_record`) rather than reviving the retired bespoke run_review producer. Reusing the recorder's already-present per-step wall-clock is extend-not-rebuild; reviving run_review would be the actual NIH.\n- No config-surface proliferation: the only new surface is two module-private frozensets in gate_dispatch.py (`_DET_STEP_IDS={\"precheck\"}`, `_LLM_STEP_KINDS={\"agent\",\"batch\"}`) — internal classification constants, not user/config toggles.\n- YAGNI honored: every emitted key (det_ms/llm_ms/total_ms/llm_calls/claim_path) serves the stated done-definition (restore the db7b AC5 dict for passive latency/cost refinement); claim_path is retained to match db7b exactly rather than invented.\n- No golden-hammer / cargo-cult / resume-driven / premature-optimization: the duration_ms timing already existed for the batch finder; this extends the same mechanism to leaf steps with a documented rationale (the tier split), and the cost proxy (criteria_count + agent step count) is a deliberate, explained approximation, not blind copying.\n- No premature abstraction: `_attach_plan_review_metrics` is a single helper called from exactly its two needed sites (happy path + coach-failure recovery), not a speculative framework."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782546211474822001,"uuid":"0493bdd2-edb4-4a25-89d5-2ee63f9f073c"}